<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Holotype ♂ (CAS): &quot;CHINA: Kwang- / tung, Summer / 1950. JL. Gressitt [p, w] // L. Gressitt / Collection [p, w] // HOLOTYPE [p] ♂ / Theopea / azurea [h] / Gressitt and Kimoto [p, r] // Theopea / azurea / holo G and K [h] / J. L. Gressitt det. [p, w] // California Academy / of Sciences / Type / No. [p] 13312 [h, w]&quot;.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on photographs). Body color (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Habitus of Pseudotheopea aeneipennis, P. azurea, and P. sufangae sp. nov. A T. aeneipennis, male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C P. aeneipennis, female, dorsal view D P. azurea, holotype, dorsal view E Same, lateral view F P. sufangae sp. nov., male, dorsal view G Same, ventral view H P. sufangae sp. nov., female, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380660" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">5D, E</figureCitation>
) bluish metallic, mouth parts and antennae dark brown; legs yellowish brown but tibiae and tarsi dark brown. Frontoclypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Heads of males of Pseudotheopea aeneipennis and P. azurea. A P. aeneipennis, dorsal view B Same, dorsofrontal view C Same, front view D P. azurea, holotype, dorsofrontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380661" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">6D</figureCitation>
) transverse and deeply excavated between eyes in males, concavity as wide as interspace between eyes, apico-lateral angles margined with long hair-like setae except along basal margin; with a pair of erect processes at center, almost reaching level of opening.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
